body:
### Version

Yosys 0.33+34

### On which OS did this happen?

Linux

### Reproduction Steps

Below Write first RTL RAM is written using blocking assignments synthesized as write first RAM.
**Yosys.ys**
read_verilog -nomem2reg asym_ram_write_first_dc.v
synth_xilinx -edif example.edif -top asym_ram_write_first_dc
write_verilog -noexpr -nodec asym_ram_write_first_dc_post_synth.v

**RTL**

module asym_ram_write_first_dc (clkB, enaB, weB, addrB,diB, doB);

parameter WIDTHB = 1;
parameter SIZEB = 8;
parameter ADDRWIDTHB = 3;

input clkB;
input weB;
input enaB;
input [ADDRWIDTHB-1:0] addrB;
input [WIDTHB-1:0] diB;
output [WIDTHB-1:0] doB;
(* ram_style = "block" *)
reg [WIDTHB-1:0] RAM [0:SIZEB-1];
reg [WIDTHB-1:0] readB;
always @(posedge clkB)
begin
    if (enaB) 
    begin
        if (weB)
            RAM[addrB] = diB;
            readB = RAM[addrB];
    end
end
assign doB = readB;

endmodule



### Expected Behavior

This RTL testcase should be synthesized in write first MODE .

### Actual Behavior

But it is synthesized as read-first MODE. As verilog-frontend somehow does not recognizes the correct read/write order in blocking assignments.
